layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 20; written lines: 19; Uniform layout. The number of lines in the margin varies considerably. The text of folios 170r-185v is written in two columns, and the commentary occupies the upper, lower and outer margin. Some of the margins are cut away. Visible pricking and hard-point ruling. Initial words written in larger decorative characters. Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable. Numerous marginal notes and additions. Censor's erasures, e.g., folios 111r, 126v.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi square and semi-cursive scripts, punctuated, of the 13th to 14th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Mahazor. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental MS 2735.'
